Field Required Type Description
results required Array<GeocodingResult> See GeocodingResult for more information.
status required GeocodingStatus See GeocodingStatus for more information.
error_message optional string A short description of the error.
plus_code optional PlusCode An encoded location reference, derived from latitude and longitude coordinates, that represents an area: 1/8000th of a degree by 1/8000th of a degree (about 14m x 14m at the equator) or smaller. Plus codes can be used as a replacement for street addresses in places where they do not exist (where buildings are not numbered or streets are not named). See Open Location Code and plus codes.See PlusCode for more information.
